SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F395A1776525067
OL,3,CManchester Piccadilly rail disruption
OL,4,Ccontinues into the weekend
OL,6,FNetwork Rail's North West route
OL,7,Fdirector, Chris Wright, said: "I am
OL,8,Fsorry to our passengers who have been
OL,9,Fimpacted by the damage to our overhead
OL,10,Fwires outside Piccadilly.
OL,12,F"The damage was sustained over a large
OL,13,Farea in a complicated location on the
OL,14,Frailway. Our engineers have worked
OL,15,Ftirelessly to fix the issue, and we
OL,16,Fworked closely with train operators to
OL,17,Foffer an amended timetable today,
OL,18,Fwhich will continue into Saturday.
OL,26,@oD@_OUtD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/7
